				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$${\text{FPKM}} = \frac{{10^{6} C}}{{{{NL} \mathord{\left/ {\vphantom {{NL} {10^{3} }}} \right. \kern-0pt} {10^{3} }}}},$$\end{document}FPKM=106CNL/103, where C and N represent the counts of mapped reads uniquely aligned to a unigene and the sum of reads sequenced that were uniquely aligned to total unigenes, respectively, and L represents the sum of a unigene in base pairs.
